<p>All hail Incinideer!</p>
<p>I could honestly have gone without the supplemental notes, I think the format standing alone is strong enough but I see the justification of leaving the door open for future Wilson's stories in this region so I don't think it's pointless to have there. Perhaps it could've been abbreviated into one log. Wilson's relentlessly chipper attitude is endearing in small doses, and it works here.</p>
<p>The format itself is great, sharing the same tone as Wilson himself but without being tied directly to the character makes all the lines about their properties very compelling. The combination of outward happiness with implied danger and sinister intent was well done.</p>

