			<div class="content" id="post-content-4320784">
									

<p>New interpretations of Wilson's Wildlife Solutions, what fun! There are a lot of little lore pieces in here that make me very happy with how people are taking WWS and just running with it &#8212; I like the idea that the SCP Foundation is monitorying anomalous communities and acting as a kind of police, but without automatically imprisoning everyone. I like WWS becoming well known enough to be shopping their expertise out to different geographical regions. That's pretty fantastic. I think it totally makes sense that the Amazon would have so much anomalous wildlife, and that Wilson's would consequently become very involved there. I like the idea of a GoI format where it's a public warning about anomalous wildlife &#8212; the magical equivalent of mountain lion warnings, saying, &quot;if you see me, don't move&quot;, and stuff like that. Basically, lots of little lore things here that I am very much enjoying.</p>
<p>If I were to have a complaint, it would be that the progression of the emails afterwords feels a bit oddly paced? Incinideer are too dangerous to let wander, okay so we'll contain them, wait we can't because natives are keeping the sanctity of their jungle, okay so you'd better come down here and set up shop 'cause this place is more anomalous than North America, alright we will. The progression is not necessarily bad, it just feels&#8230; incompletely built? I dunno.</p>
<p>In any case, it's not too large a complaint. I like <em>all</em> the ideas at play here. +1</p>
<p>P.S. This is in an alt. reality where WWS comes under Foundation supervision prior to 2008 (<a href="/the-ursus-maritimus-incident">the Ursus Maritimus Incident</a>)?</p>

							</div>

								
					
